Core Principles of RA 6713
Public Office as a Public Trust: Officials must act with responsibility, integrity, and loyalty.

Upholding Public Interest: Always prioritize the public good over personal gain.

Modest Living: Avoid lavish lifestyles that may erode public trust.

Political Neutrality: Perform duties without bias or political influence.

Transparency and Accountability: Be open and answerable to the public.

